1015
01:31:16,470 --> 01:31:20,641
Hey! That's Hisama! It's Hisama.

1016
01:31:30,484 --> 01:31:32,195
Why would you do something like this?

1017
01:31:33,613 --> 01:31:35,781
This is my only hope.

1018
01:31:36,949 --> 01:31:38,534
Please.

1019
01:31:52,173 --> 01:31:54,342
Police have taken control of the area.

1020
01:31:54,425 --> 01:31:55,676
He has started streaming.

1021
01:31:57,511 --> 01:32:02,767
We're now hearing there's a feed
from inside the facility on social media.

1022
01:32:02,850 --> 01:32:03,976
- It's Kaburagi.
- Please, you have to remember.

1023
01:32:04,727 --> 01:32:06,312
What happened on that day?

1024
01:32:06,395 --> 01:32:10,816
From our vantage point, we can't confirm
what is happening at the moment,

1025
01:32:11,400 --> 01:32:13,152
but you can see
what is happening on social media.

1026
01:32:13,778 --> 01:32:16,155
- I can't remember.
- Please, I'm begging you.

1027
01:32:18,115 --> 01:32:20,409
I need your testimony.

1028
01:32:21,410 --> 01:32:22,954
Please.

1029
01:32:31,170 --> 01:32:34,757
You saw the real perpetrator, right?

1030
01:32:59,865 --> 01:33:01,575
Hello.

1031
01:33:02,159 --> 01:33:05,288
Pardon me for the intrusion. Hello?

1032
01:33:36,610 --> 01:33:40,448
H-huh?

1033
01:33:51,250 --> 01:33:52,752
Are you okay?

1034
01:34:01,677 --> 01:34:02,845
H-hang on.

1035
01:34:02,928 --> 01:34:05,806
Stay still! Don't move.

1036
01:34:06,390 --> 01:34:08,392
- You've got it all wrong.
- Don't move.

1037
01:34:08,476 --> 01:34:10,478
- Don't move.
- It wasn't me.

1038
01:34:10,561 --> 01:34:13,731
I didn't do it.

1039
01:34:13,814 --> 01:34:16,317
- Stop resisting.
- It wasn't me.

1040
01:34:16,400 --> 01:34:18,611
If you ask her, she'll tell you.

1041
01:34:18,694 --> 01:34:21,113
I didn't do it.

1042
01:34:26,452 --> 01:34:27,828
The person who did it

1043
01:34:28,746 --> 01:34:31,665
was Kiyoto Ashikaga,
who people will have seen in the media.

1044
01:34:32,291 --> 01:34:34,960
I'm sure that you saw him, Yoshiko.

1045
01:34:59,527 --> 01:35:01,153
What the heck is he doing?

1046
01:35:02,321 --> 01:35:04,031
What the heck is he doing?
How should we respond, Matanuki?

1047
01:35:21,424 --> 01:35:22,758
Yes?

1048
01:35:22,842 --> 01:35:25,678
What are you playing at?
Get in there, now.

1049
01:35:25,761 --> 01:35:27,304
We haven't confirmed
the hostage's safety--

1050
01:35:27,388 --> 01:35:28,639
Get the fuck in there!

1051
01:35:44,572 --> 01:35:47,283
- Prepare to enter the facility!
- Yes, sir.

1052
01:36:00,045 --> 01:36:01,255
It's you.

1053
01:36:07,970 --> 01:36:09,847
This is all my fault.

1054
01:36:41,003 --> 01:36:42,546
Please, Yoshiko.

1055
01:36:45,341 --> 01:36:48,344
I didn't do it!

1056
01:36:53,349 --> 01:36:54,975
Please, I beg you.

1057
01:37:08,113 --> 01:37:10,241
On that day,

1058
01:37:12,952 --> 01:37:14,328
I…

1059
01:40:20,639 --> 01:40:23,142
361 DAYS SINCE THE ESCAPE

1060
01:40:28,981 --> 01:40:30,107
Sakai?

1061
01:40:48,876 --> 01:40:50,252
Nice to meet you.

1062
01:40:50,753 --> 01:40:52,045
Same to you.

1063
01:40:58,635 --> 01:41:02,181
Thank you once again for coming.

1064
01:41:03,182 --> 01:41:06,477
As I previously told you,
we are collecting letters of support

1065
01:41:06,560 --> 01:41:08,812
from those who knew Kaburagi.

1066
01:41:09,813 --> 01:41:10,773
Right.

1067
01:41:11,273 --> 01:41:15,861
At the facility, you heard that the
real culprit was Kiyoro Ashikaga, right?

1068
01:41:20,032 --> 01:41:23,744
It now appears that Ashikaga had hinted
at other crimes that he committed,

1069
01:41:23,827 --> 01:41:27,706
and that there were irregularities
in the account of his testimony.

1070
01:41:28,582 --> 01:41:30,834
It seems like public opinion
is also changing bit by bit.

1071
01:41:32,961 --> 01:41:36,340
We believe that Kaburagi is innocent.

1072
01:41:37,007 --> 01:41:39,635
What do you think, Sakai?

1073
01:41:41,178 --> 01:41:42,721
I…

1074
01:41:48,060 --> 01:41:49,645
think that Sakurai

1075
01:41:51,897 --> 01:41:53,440
was a nice guy,

1076
01:41:55,317 --> 01:41:57,486
and I looked up to him.

1077
01:42:00,697 --> 01:42:03,867
But in reality,

1078
01:42:04,660 --> 01:42:06,787
I didn't really know him at all.

1079
01:42:09,289 --> 01:42:12,334
I'm sure that the guy you knew, Sakurai,

1080
01:42:12,417 --> 01:42:14,920
was a reflection of who he really his.

1081
01:42:16,922 --> 01:42:20,509
Mistakes emerge when people
make judgments about others.

1082
01:42:21,802 --> 01:42:23,428
But mistakes need to be corrected.

1083
01:42:26,640 --> 01:42:32,187
I want to breathe new life
into his existence.

1084
01:42:35,440 --> 01:42:40,028
And I want people to understand
what he was really like.

1085
01:42:50,455 --> 01:42:51,582
I get it.

1086
01:43:15,105 --> 01:43:16,773
- See you.
- Later.

1087
01:43:19,526 --> 01:43:21,320
THEY ARE APPEALING FOR A RETRIAL

1088
01:43:44,635 --> 01:43:47,638
- Please sign our petition.
- Please sign our petition.

1089
01:43:47,721 --> 01:43:48,555
- Hello.
- Please help us.

1090
01:43:48,639 --> 01:43:50,432
We need your assistance.

1091
01:43:50,515 --> 01:43:51,558
- Please.
- Please

1092
01:43:51,642 --> 01:43:54,394
WAS THE NISHITOKYO MURDERER
ALSO INVOLVED IN OTHER CRIMES?

1093
01:44:11,495 --> 01:44:15,082
More and more evidence
is coming to light on Ashikaga.

1094
01:44:16,041 --> 01:44:20,671
If we made a false arrest, this
could damage the reputation of the police.

1095
01:44:22,047 --> 01:44:25,717
But please don't worry.

1096
01:44:26,593 --> 01:44:28,971
Culpability for something so serious won't
fall to you. Return to your normal duties.

1097
01:44:30,347 --> 01:44:31,390
Okay.

1098
01:44:31,932 --> 01:44:36,228
Kaburagi's escape is a major blunder
that will go down in history.

1099
01:44:36,311 --> 01:44:39,439
But it will assist us
in strengthening our efforts

1100
01:44:39,523 --> 01:44:42,734
to prevent future crimes
and deal with escapees.

1101
01:44:45,237 --> 01:44:46,488
What are you trying to say?

1102
01:44:46,989 --> 01:44:50,784
Keiichi Kaburagi was the one
who killed that family in Higashimurayama.

1103
01:44:51,743 --> 01:44:55,998
The full truth is not important
in this case.

1104
01:44:57,916 --> 01:44:59,960
You did well.

1105
01:45:00,043 --> 01:45:02,879
Just lay low and wait it out. Okay?

1106
01:45:13,223 --> 01:45:14,474
Come in.

1107
01:45:20,605 --> 01:45:21,898
Sit down.

1108
01:45:50,719 --> 01:45:52,054
It's been a while.

1109
01:45:57,142 --> 01:45:58,810
Yes, it has.

1110
01:46:08,028 --> 01:46:09,529
How are you feeling?

1111
01:46:13,241 --> 01:46:15,118
I am feeling a lot better.

1112
01:46:18,830 --> 01:46:19,915
Is that so…

1113
01:46:34,930 --> 01:46:36,515
There is one question

1114
01:46:39,059 --> 01:46:41,228
I have yet to get an answer to.

1115
01:46:44,564 --> 01:46:45,649
What is it?

1116
01:46:50,028 --> 01:46:51,613
Why did you try to escape?

1117
01:47:20,851 --> 01:47:22,978
My name is Matanuki from the
Tokyo Police's Investigation Division.

1118
01:47:24,521 --> 01:47:28,233
In the Higashimurayama murder case
involving Keiichi Kaburagi,

1119
01:47:30,068 --> 01:47:31,736
we may have charged the wrong person.

1120
01:47:37,659 --> 01:47:40,287
All responsibility for this rests with me.

1121
01:47:43,123 --> 01:47:44,708
Please be quiet.

1122
01:47:45,292 --> 01:47:47,752
I would like to have
another press conference

1123
01:47:47,836 --> 01:47:49,588
once we have
appropriately reinvestigated matters.

1124
01:47:51,256 --> 01:47:53,008
Please calm down.

1125
01:47:57,387 --> 01:48:00,265
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

1126
01:48:00,348 --> 01:48:01,850
- Thank you.
- Oh! Sayaka!

1127
01:48:05,562 --> 01:48:08,440
TOKYO POLICE ANNOUNCE REOPENING
OF HIGASHIMURAYAMA MURDER CASE

1128
01:48:08,523 --> 01:48:10,233
‪Wow. Is this for real?

1129
01:48:37,302 --> 01:48:40,597
819 DAYS SINCE THE ESCAPE

1130
01:49:14,089 --> 01:49:15,340
Stop there.

1131
01:49:24,391 --> 01:49:26,309
Why did you try to escape?

1132
01:49:36,403 --> 01:49:38,363
I wanted to believe

1133
01:49:39,739 --> 01:49:41,074
that this world was a good place.

1134
01:49:44,077 --> 01:49:45,662
I wanted to believe that

1135
01:49:46,538 --> 01:49:48,623
if I stood up for what is right,

1136
01:49:50,125 --> 01:49:52,419
people would listen to me.

1137
01:50:01,011 --> 01:50:02,721
When I got out,

1138
01:50:06,016 --> 01:50:09,602
I got a job for the first time in my life.

1139
01:50:12,564 --> 01:50:14,399
I drank alcohol

1140
01:50:16,109 --> 01:50:17,944
for the first time ever.

1141
01:50:23,283 --> 01:50:25,410
I made friends.

1142
01:50:29,205 --> 01:50:31,624
I started to like people.

1143
01:50:39,632 --> 01:50:42,677
I started to be happy to be alive.

1144
01:50:48,058 --> 01:50:49,309
And then I thought…

1145
01:50:55,065 --> 01:50:57,317
I wanted to keep on living.

1146
01:51:26,513 --> 01:51:27,931
Long time no see, Nasu.

1147
01:51:33,269 --> 01:51:34,896
Long time no see.

1148
01:51:46,616 --> 01:51:47,867
I'm sorry.

1149
01:51:49,244 --> 01:51:50,662
Don't apologize.

1150
01:51:53,081 --> 01:51:55,041
When it's all over, I'll ask you
all the questions I have.

1151
01:51:58,086 --> 01:51:59,796
When it's over?

1152
01:52:00,296 --> 01:52:01,339
What the hell, Benzo?

1153
01:52:02,715 --> 01:52:04,801
So, that's what you really look like?

1154
01:52:08,138 --> 01:52:09,222
Yes.

1155
01:52:10,682 --> 01:52:11,850
I've…

1156
01:52:13,518 --> 01:52:15,395
started studying for a qualification.

1157
01:52:16,604 --> 01:52:20,275
Isn't that cool?
You should be telling me how great I am!

1158
01:52:22,444 --> 01:52:23,862
That's incredible.

1159
01:52:32,620 --> 01:52:35,915
I'm working with Kazuya Nonomura,

1160
01:52:35,999 --> 01:52:37,542
Mai Sakai,

1161
01:52:38,376 --> 01:52:42,130
and my own father, in order
to prove your innocence.

1162
01:52:47,218 --> 01:52:48,386
I…

1163
01:52:50,930 --> 01:52:53,141
decided I'm not running away anymore.

1164
01:52:56,603 --> 01:52:59,439
I'm going to face up to both myself

1165
01:53:00,940 --> 01:53:02,650
and everyone around me.

1166
01:53:05,862 --> 01:53:07,822
It was meeting you

1167
01:53:08,948 --> 01:53:10,366
that helped me come to that decision.

1168
01:53:18,583 --> 01:53:21,044
But all I have done is run away?

1169
01:53:26,174 --> 01:53:27,717
When all of this is done,

1170
01:53:30,970 --> 01:53:32,180
let's go get some drinks.

1171
01:53:39,604 --> 01:53:40,647
Sure.

1172
01:53:41,314 --> 01:53:42,607
We'll be waiting for you…

1173
01:53:46,819 --> 01:53:48,655
Keiichi Kaburagi.

1174
01:53:51,908 --> 01:53:53,076
You are entitled to live

1175
01:53:54,244 --> 01:53:56,746
the life you have ahead of you
to the fullest.

1176
01:54:13,805 --> 01:54:14,973
Thank you.

1177
01:54:25,316 --> 01:54:27,944
Your name is Keiichi Kaburagi, correct?

1178
01:54:30,321 --> 01:54:31,364
Yes.

1179
01:54:32,657 --> 01:54:36,494
I will now deliver my verdict
on the accused, Keiichi Kaburagi,

1180
01:54:36,578 --> 01:54:43,334
who is charged with the crimes
of trespassing and murder.

1181
01:54:45,670 --> 01:54:47,046
I find the defendant…

1182
02:00:29,680 --> 02:00:32,683
